'''Dongducheon''' is a [[Administrative divisions of South Korea|city]] in [[Gyeonggi]] Province, [[South Korea]].

The city located in the north of [[Seoul]] is strategically important for the defence of the Korean capital.The main camps of the [[US Second Infantry Division]] are located in the city with the division command at [[Uijeongbu]] City. Then-[[Secretary of Defense]] [[Donald H. Rumsfeld]] toured [[Camp Casey]] at Dongducheon on [[November 18]], [[2003]].[http://www.defenselink.mil/photos/Nov2003/031118-F-2828D-028.html]

